# =============================================================================
# ‚Ü¶ ‚Äî Text and byte conversio between textus, ascii, and octeti.
# =============================================================================
#
# What this teaches:
#   ‚Ä¢ Text‚Üîbyte bridges ‚Äî `textus ‚Ü¶ octeti` (UTF-8 encode), `ascii ‚Ü¶ octeti` (ASCII encode), `octeti ‚Ü¶ textus` (UTF-8 decode), `octeti ‚Ü¶ ascii` (ASCII narrow).
#   ‚Ä¢ Fallible decoding ‚Äî byte-to-text conversions can fail on invalid bytes; recover with `‚á•`.
#   ‚Ä¢ Stdlib foundation ‚Äî these language-level bridges are what stdlib's chorda mechanical trio (pange/solve/tempta) builds on.
#
# Common mistakes:
#   ‚Ä¢ Assuming `octeti ‚Ü¶ textus` always succeeds ‚Äî invalid UTF-8 bytes require a `‚á•` recovery value.
#
# See also: ‚Ü¶, octeti, textus, chorda
# =============================================================================


# conversio ‚Äî textus/ascii ‚Üî octeti (byte conversions)
#
# WHY: `‚Ü¶ octeti` and `‚Ü¶ textus`/`‚Ü¶ ascii` are the standard Faber conversion
# paths between text and bytes. They are the language-level bridge that the
# stdlib's chorda mechanical trio (pange/solve/tempta) builds on, not a
# competitor to it. See DEFER-029 and docs/factory/octeti-unify-lista/.
#
# textus ‚Ü¶ octeti: UTF-8 encode (lossless; String is already UTF-8 in Rust).
# ascii  ‚Ü¶ octeti: ASCII encode (lossless; ASCII is a strict subset of UTF-8).
# octeti ‚Ü¶ textus: UTF-8 decode (can fail on invalid bytes; use `‚á•` to recover).
# octeti ‚Ü¶ ascii:  ASCII narrow (can fail on any byte ‚â• 128; use `‚á•`).

incipit {
    # textus ‚Üí octeti (UTF-8 encode)
    fixum textus hi ‚Üê "hi"
    fixum octeti enc ‚Üê hi ‚Ü¶ octeti
    nota enc.longitudo()

    # octeti ‚Üí textus (UTF-8 decode, valid bytes)
    # "hi" in UTF-8
    fixum octeti raw ‚Üê |68 69|
    fixum textus dec ‚Üê raw ‚Ü¶ textus
    nota dec

    # octeti ‚Üí textus with recovery (invalid UTF-8 ‚Üí recovery value)
    fixum octeti badUtf8 ‚Üê |ff ff|
    fixum textus recovered ‚Üê badUtf8 ‚Ü¶ textus ‚á• "?"
    nota recovered

    # ascii ‚Üí octeti
    fixum ascii a ‚Üê 'hi'
    fixum octeti aenc ‚Üê a ‚Ü¶ octeti
    nota aenc.longitudo()

    # octeti ‚Üí ascii (valid ASCII bytes)
    fixum ascii adec ‚Üê raw ‚Ü¶ ascii
    nota adec

    # octeti ‚Üí ascii with recovery (non-ASCII byte ‚Üí recovery value)
    fixum octeti nonAscii ‚Üê |ff|
    fixum ascii arecovery ‚Üê nonAscii ‚Ü¶ ascii ‚á• 'x'
    nota arecovery
}
